Compiz is a compositing window manager.

==Install==
===Preinstall===

First compiz must be keyworded in, and use flags set to pull in emerald.
{{RootCmd|<pre>echo "x11-plugins/compiz-plugins-main" >> /etc/portage/package.accept_keywords
echo "x11-libs/compiz-bcop" >> /etc/portage/package.accept_keywords
echo "x11-wm/compiz-fusion" >> /etc/portage/package.accept_keywords
echo "x11-plugins/compiz-plugins-extra" >> /etc/portage/package.accept_keywords
echo "x11-libs/libcompizconfig" >> /etc/portage/package.accept_keywords
echo "x11-wm/compiz" >> /etc/portage/package.accept_keywords
echo "dev-python/compizconfig-python" >> /etc/portage/package.accept_keywords
echo "x11-libs/compizconfig-backend-gconf" >> /etc/portage/package.accept_keywords
echo "x11-wm/emerald" >> /etc/portage/package.accept_keywords
echo "x11-themes/emerald-themes" >> /etc/portage/package.accept_keywords
echo "x11-apps/fusion-icon" >> /etc/portage/package.accept_keywords
echo "x11-apps/ccsm" >> /etc/portage/package.accept_keywords
echo "x11-wm/compiz-fusion emerald" >> /etc/portage/package.use</pre>}}

===Backend===

Install a backend that is appropriate to your system, or both.  Failure to do so might result in unstable compiz behavior.
{{emerge|x11-libs/compizconfig-backend-gconf}}
or
{{emerge|x11-libs/compizconfig-backend-kconfig4}}

===Emerge===
{{emerge|compiz-fusion fusion-icon ccsm}}

==Setup==

Press alt + f2
Enter "fusion-icon"
Then run.

Right click the fusion-icon and select "settings manager"

Some options must be selected as ccsm's default configuration is empty.  These will get you off on the right foot.

Turn on

"Effects"
<pre>Window Decoration</pre>

"window management"
<pre>Move Window, Resize Window, & Application Switcher</pre>

